tress on its side.";i:19;s:52:"Roll the edge of the sheet on your side and grab it.";i:20;s:85:"Pull the sheet up so the person slowly rolls from his or her back to his or her side.";i:21;s:106:"Place pillows behind the persons back and buttocks to help keep him or her on his or her side comfortably.";i:22;s:43:"Smooth the sheets so they are not wrinkled.";i:23;s:42:"Pull the bed rail up so it locks in place.";i:24;s:162:"Move to the other side of the bed and now pull the slide-sheet laterally so that you can bring the patient with that lateral manoeuvre into the middle of the bed.";i:25;s:62:"Things to consider when assessing how to turn a patient alone.";i:26;s:37:"The dependency of the person and the.";i:27;s:101:"Flipping a mattress involves turning it over allowing you to sleep on the other side of the mattress.";i:28;s:91:"To do this you would rotate the mattress 90 degrees and so that it is hanging over one end.";i:29;s:102:"Then you raise the mattress on its edge and lower the mattress over so that the other side is face up.";i:30;s:42:"Then turn the mattress 90 degrees further.";i:31;s:90:"Once you have rotated your mattress flip needing mattress will need that you turn it over.";i:32;s:30:"Flip your mattress if need be.";i:33;s:69:"There will be a need for your mattress to be flipped once in a while.";i:34;s:71:"To do this you will need to pull it to either side of your bed so that.";i:35;s:72:"Flipping your mattress used to be a pain and caused frequent complaints.";i:36;s:160:"Mattress Firm remembers the struggle -- you had to remove all the pillows and sheets wrestle it to the ground flip it over then hoist it back on top of the bed.";i:37;s:81:"It was hard enough to do with two people and nearly impossible to do by yourself.";i:38;s:137:"Rotating your new mattress on a regular basis will prolong the life of your bed in order to continue to give you the best sleep possible.";i:39;s:50:"Read the 4-step process to rotating your mattress.";i:40;s:128:"In t